/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-strategizer-step-004.log:4389:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md:42:The attacker is right that "small exact packet" should not be the only admissible test regime, and that an honest parameter family or finite-time scale-separated construction may be necessary. The critique is also right that banning all asymptotic structure would be too strong.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-strategizer-step-004.log:4390:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md:50:This lands cleanly. The original edge-case list is heavily inherited from the prior non-isolability narrative, so it is not a neutral stress test. The attacker is right that the audit must include cases favorable to the opposite conclusion as well: engineered helical sign patterns, sparse triad geometries, scale-separated families, and cases where leakage exists but is dynamically negligible.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-strategizer-step-004.log:4391:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:21:The attacker is right that a theorem proved only for minimal packets may miss redundancy, distributed role assignment, or small tails. The attacker is also right that a forced ledger can overstate importance if it counts channels that are dynamically negligible or cancellation-prone. But starting with minimal packets is still a reasonable calibration move. The defect was not using them first; it was letting them implicitly define the whole theorem class.
