/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-007-judge-03.log:141:- Action: require the candidate to control more than a thin favorable interaction class, or else quantify exactly how much of the relevant transfer it captures.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-007-judge-03.log:208:- "Near-coherent helicity sign" is already suspicious. Coherent sign is close to the same aligned or polarized regimes that prior helical-decimation literature makes look favorable. Unless the chain proves that such coherence captures a quantitatively non-negligible part of the full bad transfer, it has not escaped thin-regime folklore.
