/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-007-judge-03.log:212:- The quantity "more than a thin favorable interaction class" is not operational. The relevant question is not whether the class is thin in an aesthetic sense, but whether it carries enough of the full nonlinear burden near the endpoint being targeted. Without that calibration, Step 3 can certify a regime that is large in one bookkeeping sense and irrelevant in theorem terms.
