/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-007-judge-03.log:233:- The "first missing lemma" is likely not a routine gap. It is likely the entire hard problem: proving that any favorable energy-helicity geometry persists, localizes, and dominates the bad full-equation interactions.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-007-judge-03.log:235:- The final kill condition is good. If the output still reads as "helicity is interesting," the chain has failed. But the chain should also reject any final claim that reads as "if the solution stays in a strongly polarized helicity regime, then maybe things improve," because that is usually just a dressed-up restatement of the favorable regime.
