/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-planner.log:1163:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:50:- The perturbation test around favorable helicity or resonance classes is likely fatal. Full Navier-Stokes does not let one isolate clean same-helicity or near-resonant sectors for free. If the gain is only visible on a thin interaction set, then the chain is probably seeing a regime artifact, not a structural mechanism.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-planner.log:1186:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:42:Concrete failure mode: Step 3 may produce an inequality that looks favorable in an exact or nearly exact Beltrami regime, then collapse outside that regime. At that point the chain has not found an SQG-type mechanism; it has merely recovered the known statement that special alignment depletes the nonlinearity.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-planner.log:1206:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selected/chain-02.md:51:- Action: test whether the claimed gain survives perturbation away from exactly favorable helicity or resonance classes.
