/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-planner.log:1371:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/refined/chain-02.md:55:- Action: perturb away from exactly favorable helicity or resonance classes and determine whether the gain reflects true structure or only a narrow regime artifact.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-planner.log:1765:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:39:- "Near-coherent helicity sign" is already suspicious. Coherent sign is close to the same aligned or polarized regimes that prior helical-decimation literature makes look favorable. Unless the chain proves that such coherence captures a quantitatively non-negligible part of the full bad transfer, it has not escaped thin-regime folklore.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-planner.log:1767:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:51:- Mixed-helicity interactions are not a perturbation of the good regime. They are the default full-equation environment. If the gain depends on coherent helicity sign or favorable polarization, then mixed-helicity restoration is not one late test among many. It is the central obstacle and should have been front-loaded.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-planner.log:1771:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:57:Failure mode: Step 4 shows that every apparent gain lived in sign-coherent, filtered, or poorly localized sectors, while the actual full equation keeps the dangerous transfer in mixed or low-helicity regions.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-planner.log:1773:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:64:- The "first missing lemma" is likely not a routine gap. It is likely the entire hard problem: proving that any favorable energy-helicity geometry persists, localizes, and dominates the bad full-equation interactions.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-planner.log:1775:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:66:- The final kill condition is good. If the output still reads as "helicity is interesting," the chain has failed. But the chain should also reject any final claim that reads as "if the solution stays in a strongly polarized helicity regime, then maybe things improve," because that is usually just a dressed-up restatement of the favorable regime.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-planner.log:1780:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:90:The route lives next to helical triad analysis, decimated models, Waleffe-type interaction lore, and familiar statements that favorable helicity polarization depletes transfer in restricted sectors. Without an early novelty threshold, the chain can spend a lot of effort rediscovering that the favorable regime looks favorable.
